Privacy Policy
Phone Locator respects your privacy and is committed to protecting any information you provide while using our app. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and disclose your personal information.
Our main aim is to ensure you that we will protect your personal information that we needed in order to provide our services and to apprise you about our rules and regulations. We provide this Privacy Policy to help you understand how we collect, use, divulge, transfer, and store your information that we access in order to provide our services. For using this app without any disruption, while using our service, we will suggest you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information. We will only collect information where it is reasonably necessary to do for the conduct of our app. We don't sell your personal information to third parties and donâ€™t store your information without your prior consent. When you use our services, you are trusting us with your information. We understand this is a big responsibility so we will work hard to protect your information and put you in control. Personal Information taken by us will be lawful and will not be conspicuous. Since no information communicated over the Internet or put away on the Internet, clients can be destined to be totally secure.
Information We Collect
-
Contact List Information:
We may collect and upload your contact list information for the purpose of number locating only.
-
Device Information:
We may collect information about your device, including but not limited to device type, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.
How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect, including your contact list information, to:
- Provide and improve our services.
- Customize and personalize your experience.
- Communicate with you, including responding to your inquiries and providing customer support.
Disclosure of Information
We may disclose your information:
- To third-party service providers who assist us in providing and maintaining our services.
- In response to legal requests or to comply with applicable laws and regulations.
- With your consent or as otherwise disclosed at the time of collection.
Data Retention
We will retain your information only for as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or as required by law.
Your Choices
You can choose not to provide certain information, although it may limit your ability to use certain features of the app.
Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated policy on our app.
